1
00:00:49,385 --> 00:00:51,305
<i>In the end, you chose me.</i>

2
00:00:52,745 --> 00:00:54,065
You've got such a mouth.
Let me teach you a lesson.

3
00:00:56,425 --> 00:00:58,225
A boy!

4
00:00:58,305 --> 00:01:01,025
We got a boy!

5
00:01:01,105 --> 00:01:05,545
If you want to quit your job
and start your own company, you can.

6
00:01:05,624 --> 00:01:07,865
<i>Then you deserve a reward.</i>

7
00:01:16,025 --> 00:01:17,585
I can't. I can't do it.

8
00:01:17,665 --> 00:01:19,025
I can't do it.

9
00:01:19,105 --> 00:01:20,705
-Nueng.
-I can't.

10
00:01:20,785 --> 00:01:22,665
-Nueng.
-What do I do?

11
00:01:23,705 --> 00:01:25,265
-What do I do?
-Nueng.

12
00:01:25,345 --> 00:01:27,385
-I'm here.
-How am I supposed to live?

13
00:01:27,465 --> 00:01:29,225
It's okay.

14
00:01:29,985 --> 00:01:30,865
You're okay.

15
00:01:30,945 --> 00:01:32,545
Let's take deep breaths together, okay?

16
00:01:32,625 --> 00:01:35,185
Take a deep breath.

17
00:01:35,905 --> 00:01:38,425
I can't clean up the vase.

18
00:01:38,505 --> 00:01:41,025
It's okay. I'll clean it up for you.

19
00:01:41,945 --> 00:01:43,465
Do you want to take your medicine?

20
00:01:44,345 --> 00:01:47,465
Medicine? Take medicine?

21
00:01:47,545 --> 00:01:49,985
No, I can't.

22
00:01:50,065 --> 00:01:52,065
Phupha's here. I can't take it.

23
00:01:52,145 --> 00:01:54,505
Oon, can you make her
something sweet to drink, please?

24
00:01:54,585 --> 00:01:56,785
Then how am I supposed
to raise him properly?

25
00:01:57,345 --> 00:01:58,425
I can't take medicine.

26
00:01:58,505 --> 00:02:01,505
-Try touching your baby.
-I can't do anything.

27
00:02:01,585 --> 00:02:04,305
Touch your baby. Touch your baby.

28
00:02:07,865 --> 00:02:10,625
Can you feel Phupha?

29
00:02:13,185 --> 00:02:15,145
-Can you feel him?
-Yeah.

30
00:02:15,225 --> 00:02:17,945
Phupha's moving.

31
00:02:18,665 --> 00:02:20,505
I'm sorry. Mommy's sorry.

32
00:02:21,185 --> 00:02:23,745
Mommy can't take care of you properly.

33
00:02:23,825 --> 00:02:26,185
I'm sorry. I can't do it.

34
00:02:26,265 --> 00:02:27,345
I can't raise you well.

35
00:02:27,425 --> 00:02:29,745
It's okay, Nueng. Take a deep breath.

36
00:02:29,825 --> 00:02:31,105
Deep breaths.

37
00:02:31,625 --> 00:02:33,385
Breathe with me, okay?

38
00:02:34,265 --> 00:02:35,145
Alright.

39
00:02:35,785 --> 00:02:36,825
Here's the sweet drink.

40
00:02:36,905 --> 00:02:37,985
Thank you.

41
00:02:39,225 --> 00:02:40,545
Take a few sips.

42
00:02:41,785 --> 00:02:42,825
Just a little.

43
00:02:49,505 --> 00:02:51,785
Good job. You're doing great.

44
00:02:53,025 --> 00:02:54,105
Alright.

45
00:02:55,105 --> 00:02:57,745
Breathe in. Take a deep breath.

46
00:02:59,105 --> 00:03:02,625
One, two,

47
00:03:03,945 --> 00:03:05,225
three.

48
00:03:05,905 --> 00:03:08,225
Hold it. One,

49
00:03:08,945 --> 00:03:10,185
two,

50
00:03:11,145 --> 00:03:12,425
three,

51
00:03:13,145 --> 00:03:14,385
four.

52
00:03:14,465 --> 00:03:16,065
Now slowly breathe out.

53
00:03:22,465 --> 00:03:25,945
Panic disorder? Since when?

54
00:03:27,665 --> 00:03:30,425
Probably around two or three months ago.

55
00:03:30,505 --> 00:03:32,505
Back when I would take Nueng
to her prenatal appointments,

56
00:03:32,585 --> 00:03:36,625
she'd get really anxious.
Her hands and feet would go cold,

57
00:03:37,465 --> 00:03:38,545
and her heart would race.

58
00:03:39,105 --> 00:03:41,025
So we consulted a doctor.

59
00:03:41,105 --> 00:03:43,265
But after the physical examination,

60
00:03:43,345 --> 00:03:45,865
nothing seemed physically wrong.

61
00:03:45,945 --> 00:03:48,785
So the doctor suggested
we see a psychiatrist instead.

62
00:03:50,425 --> 00:03:54,465
That's when we found out
she has panic disorder.

63
00:03:57,625 --> 00:03:59,105
How did she get that?

64
00:03:59,785 --> 00:04:03,385
I think the main reason is because
she can't rely on herself right now.

65
00:04:04,185 --> 00:04:07,705
Nueng probably planned to move back
to Thailand and start working,

66
00:04:08,665 --> 00:04:11,265
but then her morning sickness
got severe, so she couldn't work.

67
00:04:12,145 --> 00:04:14,745
And once she started feeling better,
her belly was already too big.

68
00:04:14,825 --> 00:04:16,504
Moving around became difficult.

69
00:04:20,345 --> 00:04:21,825
Most importantly,

70
00:04:22,825 --> 00:04:25,185
she's scared she won't be a good mother.

71
00:04:33,105 --> 00:04:35,825
I've been living in the same house as her,

72
00:04:35,905 --> 00:04:37,905
but I didn't notice any of this.

73
00:04:40,745 --> 00:04:42,625
I'm sorry, Fun.

74
00:04:44,505 --> 00:04:46,185
It's okay.

75
00:04:46,265 --> 00:04:49,865
Didn't you once tell me that
we were going to build a family together?

76
00:04:49,945 --> 00:04:53,865
You'd build from the front of the house,
and I'd build from the back.

77
00:04:53,945 --> 00:04:57,985
And one day, we'd meet in the middle
and become a complete home.

78
00:04:58,505 --> 00:04:59,985
Our family.

79
00:05:10,345 --> 00:05:12,785
I'm really lucky

80
00:05:12,865 --> 00:05:14,625
to have you as my life partner.

81
00:05:20,225 --> 00:05:21,345
-Oon.
-Hmm?

82
00:05:22,025 --> 00:05:23,825
I think I'm going to resign.

83
00:05:27,185 --> 00:05:31,105
Everything in our life right now
feels like it's falling into place.

84
00:05:32,545 --> 00:05:35,225
I'm finally about to start doing
what I've always wanted to do.

85
00:05:36,105 --> 00:05:37,745
And most importantly,

86
00:05:38,265 --> 00:05:40,825
our house is about
to have a little one too.

87
00:05:41,425 --> 00:05:44,545
I'll finally have time
to help take care of Phupha.

88
00:05:46,585 --> 00:05:48,625
Such a planner.

89
00:06:07,225 --> 00:06:08,785
Oon-oon, are you sure you'll be okay?

90
00:06:09,865 --> 00:06:11,225
Maybe I shouldn't go after all.

91
00:06:12,385 --> 00:06:13,705
I'll be fine.

92
00:06:13,785 --> 00:06:17,345
Now that I know what's going on
with Nueng, I can handle it.

93
00:06:18,385 --> 00:06:20,265
I survived dealing with you, didn't I?

94
00:06:20,345 --> 00:06:22,945
Oops, that was the voice in my head.

95
00:06:23,025 --> 00:06:24,705
Hey!

96
00:06:31,705 --> 00:06:34,065
Oon-oon, how much cash
do you have left right now?

97
00:06:34,945 --> 00:06:36,185
Cash?

98
00:06:37,985 --> 00:06:40,025
Probably around 500 baht.

99
00:06:42,825 --> 00:06:47,145
Then make it last until the end
of the month. I'm not giving you more.

100
00:06:47,225 --> 00:06:48,265
Huh?

101
00:06:48,785 --> 00:06:51,425
Fun, it's only the middle of the month.

102
00:06:51,505 --> 00:06:53,425
I thought you said you could handle it.

103
00:06:53,945 --> 00:06:55,585
Not this.

104
00:06:55,665 --> 00:06:58,385
Fun, are you serious?

105
00:06:58,465 --> 00:06:59,985
You're joking, right?

106
00:07:00,905 --> 00:07:02,665
That's all I'm saying. I'm off now.

107
00:07:07,945 --> 00:07:09,025
Five hundred?

108
00:07:14,145 --> 00:07:15,185
Sit here.

109
00:07:17,745 --> 00:07:19,385
Careful. Slowly.

110
00:08:05,785 --> 00:08:09,065
-I'll do it for you.
-It's okay. I can do it.

111
00:08:09,145 --> 00:08:11,265
I'll do it.

112
00:08:11,945 --> 00:08:13,065
Nueng,

113
00:08:14,425 --> 00:08:15,785
from now on,

114
00:08:15,865 --> 00:08:17,665
if there's anything you can't handle,

115
00:08:17,745 --> 00:08:20,265
tell me, and I'll do it for you.

116
00:08:22,985 --> 00:08:26,345
No matter what it is, I'll do it.

117
00:08:34,705 --> 00:08:35,585
Okay?

118
00:09:11,745 --> 00:09:13,185
If I had an older sister,

119
00:09:14,745 --> 00:09:16,105
she'd probably be like you.

120
00:09:25,625 --> 00:09:27,545
Older sister is fine.

121
00:09:27,625 --> 00:09:30,345
But if you call me grandma again,
you can get out.

122
00:09:34,345 --> 00:09:35,465
Whoa.

123
00:09:54,105 --> 00:09:55,705
SINGLE MOTHER WITH NOWHERE TO TURN

124
00:09:55,785 --> 00:09:59,225
STEALS FROM CONVENIENCE STORE
TO KEEP 7-MONTH-OLD BABY ALIVE

125
00:10:15,665 --> 00:10:17,225
Nueng.

126
00:10:17,825 --> 00:10:19,985
Nueng, I'm here.

127
00:10:21,545 --> 00:10:22,705
I'm here.

128
00:10:24,185 --> 00:10:25,145
Nueng.

129
00:10:28,265 --> 00:10:31,105
Nueng, Nueng, Nueng.

130
00:10:33,385 --> 00:10:34,225
Nueng.

131
00:10:36,105 --> 00:10:37,185
Can you feel this?

132
00:10:37,265 --> 00:10:39,105
This is your hand.

133
00:10:40,225 --> 00:10:41,905
This is your hand.

134
00:10:44,625 --> 00:10:46,385
This is your arm.

135
00:10:49,185 --> 00:10:52,465
Your arm. Can you feel it?

136
00:10:57,545 --> 00:10:58,705
Arm…

137
00:11:00,225 --> 00:11:01,065
Arm…

138
00:11:01,745 --> 00:11:03,425
Do you want to hold my hand, Nueng?

139
00:11:32,785 --> 00:11:35,625
I'm here. I'm right here.

140
00:11:38,905 --> 00:11:41,705
Remember what I told you before?

141
00:11:44,865 --> 00:11:46,545
If there's anything you can't handle,

142
00:11:46,625 --> 00:11:48,345
I'll do it for you.

143
00:11:49,305 --> 00:11:50,945
No matter what it is,

144
00:11:51,505 --> 00:11:52,945
I'll take care of it.

145
00:12:00,705 --> 00:12:02,945
Throw it all at me.

146
00:12:04,265 --> 00:12:05,505
Just tell me.

147
00:12:06,145 --> 00:12:08,505
Let me carry it all for you.

148
00:12:11,745 --> 00:12:14,025
Just don't let go of us, okay?

149
00:12:21,505 --> 00:12:24,945
Now let's breathe together.

150
00:12:26,425 --> 00:12:27,625
One,

151
00:12:28,665 --> 00:12:29,785
two,

152
00:12:33,665 --> 00:12:35,145
three,

153
00:12:36,225 --> 00:12:37,625
four.

154
00:12:37,705 --> 00:12:39,185
Hold it…

155
00:12:40,385 --> 00:12:43,625
One, two,

156
00:12:45,545 --> 00:12:46,785
three,

157
00:12:47,985 --> 00:12:51,545
four, five.

158
00:13:05,265 --> 00:13:06,865
What happened?

159
00:13:06,945 --> 00:13:08,785
You couldn't hold it in?

160
00:13:08,865 --> 00:13:11,705
I think my water just broke.

161
00:13:11,785 --> 00:13:13,745
Your water broke?

162
00:13:13,825 --> 00:13:15,985
Her water broke! What do we do?

163
00:13:16,065 --> 00:13:18,345
-I'll get the car ready.
-Get the car ready.

164
00:13:18,425 --> 00:13:20,625
-I'll go get the keys.
-No, Fun.

165
00:13:20,705 --> 00:13:23,865
You need to grab the bag.
I'll get the keys myself.

166
00:13:23,945 --> 00:13:25,105
Okay. Hey, Oon.

167
00:13:25,185 --> 00:13:26,545
The key is not there.

168
00:13:26,625 --> 00:13:28,305
Oh, right.

169
00:13:28,385 --> 00:13:30,345
I'm going to get the bag, okay?
Stay right here.

170
00:13:30,425 --> 00:13:31,785
Wait.

171
00:13:31,865 --> 00:13:33,785
-Clothes.
-Clothes?

172
00:13:33,865 --> 00:13:35,785
-Okay, okay. Clothes.
-Yeah.

173
00:13:39,985 --> 00:13:43,025
-I'm back. Here are the keys.
-Okay.

174
00:13:43,105 --> 00:13:44,945
I got clothes.

175
00:13:45,025 --> 00:13:46,945
Fun, these are your clothes.

176
00:13:48,145 --> 00:13:50,345
I'll go get them. Here, the keys.

177
00:13:50,425 --> 00:13:51,825
Oh.

178
00:13:51,905 --> 00:13:54,065
Oon, bring the other bag too, okay?

179
00:13:54,145 --> 00:13:54,985
Okay.

180
00:13:55,065 --> 00:13:56,785
The bag. The other bag.

181
00:14:00,025 --> 00:14:01,785
Here, clothes. Change now.

182
00:14:01,865 --> 00:14:04,065
Wait, wait, wait.

183
00:14:04,145 --> 00:14:05,745
I'll change in the bathroom.

184
00:14:05,825 --> 00:14:06,825
Bathroom.

185
00:14:06,905 --> 00:14:08,345
-Let's go.
-I'll carry this for you.

186
00:14:09,345 --> 00:14:10,185
Oh.

187
00:14:11,025 --> 00:14:12,825
Slowly.

188
00:14:12,905 --> 00:14:14,425
Be careful.

189
00:14:17,305 --> 00:14:20,225
No, you can't come in.

190
00:14:24,505 --> 00:14:25,345
Here.

191
00:14:26,545 --> 00:14:28,745
Be careful.

192
00:14:28,825 --> 00:14:29,865
Thank you.

193
00:14:31,185 --> 00:14:32,625
Alright. Okay.

194
00:14:43,665 --> 00:14:44,505
Wait. Where's Nueng?

195
00:14:44,585 --> 00:14:45,425
Nueng!

196
00:14:45,505 --> 00:14:47,745
Wait for me. Where are you going?

197
00:14:47,825 --> 00:14:49,185
-You didn't even wait.
-Nueng.

198
00:14:49,265 --> 00:14:50,465
Hold on.

199
00:14:50,545 --> 00:14:52,385
-Nueng.
-Wait.

200
00:14:52,465 --> 00:14:54,185
-I can't.
-Slowly.

201
00:14:54,265 --> 00:14:55,705
-Open the door.
-Wait.

202
00:14:55,785 --> 00:14:57,345
Open the door.

203
00:14:57,425 --> 00:14:58,465
Get in.

204
00:15:00,825 --> 00:15:02,425
-Alright.
-Wait!

205
00:15:02,505 --> 00:15:04,385
The bag!

206
00:15:04,465 --> 00:15:05,585
Go get the bag.

207
00:15:06,185 --> 00:15:07,385
The bag.

208
00:15:08,905 --> 00:15:10,105
-Got it.
-Okay, the bag.

209
00:15:10,185 --> 00:15:11,385
We're going now, okay?

210
00:15:11,465 --> 00:15:12,985
Okay. Go.

211
00:15:20,345 --> 00:15:23,505
You're doing great, Mommy.
We can see the baby's head now.

212
00:15:23,585 --> 00:15:24,825
Push, okay?

213
00:15:24,905 --> 00:15:26,625
Deep breath, hold it, push.

214
00:16:11,785 --> 00:16:12,985
Nueng's here.

215
00:16:40,865 --> 00:16:42,985
How are you feeling?

216
00:16:44,185 --> 00:16:45,745
It hurt like crazy.

217
00:16:46,825 --> 00:16:47,985
But

218
00:16:48,585 --> 00:16:50,945
once I saw my baby's face,

219
00:16:51,025 --> 00:16:52,985
all the pain just disappeared.

220
00:16:55,265 --> 00:16:57,465
So this is what they call

221
00:16:57,545 --> 00:16:59,585
"beautiful pain."

222
00:17:02,545 --> 00:17:04,065
You did great, Mommy.

223
00:17:06,345 --> 00:17:07,464
Mommy…

224
00:17:09,665 --> 00:17:11,545
The baby's here.

225
00:17:15,585 --> 00:17:17,385
He's so tiny.

226
00:17:18,985 --> 00:17:20,905
So cute.

227
00:17:20,985 --> 00:17:23,985
Oon, you're supposed
to say "adorably ugly."

228
00:17:25,464 --> 00:17:28,585
So adorably ugly, little one.

229
00:17:31,025 --> 00:17:34,385
You should try breastfeeding now, okay?
It'll help stimulate milk production.

230
00:17:34,465 --> 00:17:35,385
Okay.

231
00:17:56,145 --> 00:17:58,625
The first milk that comes out
after giving birth is called colostrum.

232
00:17:58,705 --> 00:18:00,545
It's the best thing for the baby.

233
00:18:00,625 --> 00:18:01,625
I see.

234
00:18:35,065 --> 00:18:37,185
Fun, do you want to hold him?

235
00:18:50,265 --> 00:18:52,425
You're so adorably ugly.

236
00:18:56,745 --> 00:19:01,505
Welcome to the family, Phupha.

237
00:19:09,865 --> 00:19:13,025
We finally get to meet you, Phupha.

238
00:19:26,465 --> 00:19:27,865
He's full now.

239
00:19:27,945 --> 00:19:30,905
-All full and already sleepy?
-Already sleepy.

240
00:19:37,545 --> 00:19:39,185
He's asleep.

241
00:19:41,665 --> 00:19:44,145
-Oon, Oon.
-What's wrong?

242
00:19:44,225 --> 00:19:46,825
I don't know what's happening.

243
00:19:46,905 --> 00:19:48,385
I can't breathe. My chest feels tight.

244
00:19:48,465 --> 00:19:50,305
You can't breathe?

245
00:19:50,385 --> 00:19:52,625
Oon, go get the nurse now.

246
00:19:52,705 --> 00:19:54,105
Hang on.

247
00:19:54,185 --> 00:19:55,825
I'll get the nurse right away.

248
00:19:56,585 --> 00:19:57,745
Oon.

249
00:19:58,625 --> 00:20:02,105
The patient's having trouble breathing.
Can someone come check on her, please?

250
00:20:02,185 --> 00:20:03,225
<i>Yes.</i>

251
00:20:07,225 --> 00:20:08,825
Oon, Fun.

252
00:20:10,225 --> 00:20:11,905
I'm here. I'm right here.

253
00:20:13,905 --> 00:20:14,905
I'm here.

254
00:20:32,225 --> 00:20:35,785
Doctor, the patient in Room 101
is experiencing respiratory distress.

255
00:20:36,385 --> 00:20:39,025
BP 94/62. Heart rate 110.

256
00:20:39,105 --> 00:20:42,505
Oxygen saturation 90 on room air.

257
00:20:42,585 --> 00:20:46,385
Yes, Doctor. Oxygen mask with bag at ten
liters per minute. Transferring to ICU.

258
00:21:00,065 --> 00:21:01,145
Nueng.

259
00:21:01,945 --> 00:21:03,945
-Oon.
-I'm here.

260
00:21:04,865 --> 00:21:06,625
Take care of Phupha for me.

261
00:21:15,665 --> 00:21:18,585
-Nueng.
-Nueng.

262
00:21:18,665 --> 00:21:19,585
Nueng!

263
00:21:20,105 --> 00:21:21,825
No pulse. Patient's having cardiac arrest.

264
00:21:23,105 --> 00:21:24,185
Nueng.

265
00:21:27,425 --> 00:21:29,305
Nueng.

266
00:21:32,265 --> 00:21:34,105
-Nueng.
-Nueng.

267
00:21:34,185 --> 00:21:36,785
-Nueng.
-Nueng.

268
00:21:40,145 --> 00:21:41,105
Nueng.

269
00:21:43,665 --> 00:21:45,145
Nueng.

270
00:21:48,865 --> 00:21:50,105
Excuse us.

271
00:21:54,465 --> 00:21:55,425
She'll be fine.

272
00:22:01,985 --> 00:22:02,985
Checking pulse.

273
00:22:05,145 --> 00:22:06,305
No pulse detected.

274
00:22:06,385 --> 00:22:07,945
EKG shows V-fib.

275
00:22:10,945 --> 00:22:12,345
Nueng has to be okay.

276
00:22:21,145 --> 00:22:22,225
Prepare to shock.

277
00:22:22,305 --> 00:22:24,625
Defibrillation, 200 joules.

278
00:22:27,185 --> 00:22:30,225
Shock. Start CPR.

279
00:22:43,705 --> 00:22:45,665
Prepare defibrillation, 200 joules.

280
00:22:50,145 --> 00:22:51,385
Shock.

281
00:23:02,745 --> 00:23:04,425
Are you relatives of Ms. Kanyawee?

282
00:23:04,505 --> 00:23:05,545
Yes.

283
00:23:05,625 --> 00:23:08,025
I'm very sorry for your loss.

284
00:23:08,105 --> 00:23:09,585
The patient passed away

285
00:23:09,665 --> 00:23:13,185
at 3.10 p.m. The cause of death

286
00:23:13,265 --> 00:23:16,825
is suspected to be
amniotic fluid embolism,

287
00:23:16,905 --> 00:23:19,505
which is a severe condition
that progresses very rapidly.

288
00:23:19,585 --> 00:23:22,345
Our medical team did everything we could,

289
00:23:22,425 --> 00:23:25,145
but unfortunately,
we were unable to save her.

290
00:23:26,065 --> 00:23:27,745
Please accept our condolences.

291
00:23:35,105 --> 00:23:35,985
Nueng…

292
00:23:36,665 --> 00:23:37,585
Oon…

293
00:23:40,025 --> 00:23:41,425
It's not true, right?

294
00:23:43,305 --> 00:23:44,865
It's not true, right, Oon?

295
00:24:15,265 --> 00:24:16,225
Oon.

296
00:24:17,345 --> 00:24:19,385
-Mom.
-What happened?

297
00:24:19,465 --> 00:24:20,945
Nueng already gave birth, right?

298
00:24:26,705 --> 00:24:28,025
Nueng…

299
00:24:29,505 --> 00:24:31,465
Nueng's dead, Mom.

300
00:24:41,305 --> 00:24:42,305
Nueng…

301
00:24:45,265 --> 00:24:47,505
Mom. Mom.

302
00:24:52,065 --> 00:24:52,905
Mom.

303
00:24:59,425 --> 00:25:00,865
Can we get some ammonia, please?

304
00:25:05,385 --> 00:25:06,625
Thank you.

305
00:25:08,545 --> 00:25:10,865
If you need anything,
just call for a nurse, okay?

306
00:25:17,825 --> 00:25:19,345
How could this happen?

307
00:25:19,905 --> 00:25:21,345
How did Nueng die?

308
00:25:23,385 --> 00:25:24,385
She…

309
00:25:25,145 --> 00:25:29,385
The doctor said
it was an amniotic fluid embolism, Mom.

310
00:25:29,465 --> 00:25:30,945
Oh, Nueng…

311
00:25:33,865 --> 00:25:35,825
What about the baby? How's the baby?

312
00:25:35,905 --> 00:25:38,865
The baby's safe.
He's in the nursery right now.

313
00:25:40,505 --> 00:25:44,425
Nueng, why was your fate so cruel?

314
00:25:51,505 --> 00:25:52,585
Nueng…

315
00:25:57,065 --> 00:25:58,225
Fun,

316
00:25:58,305 --> 00:26:00,345
we have to stay strong.

317
00:26:00,865 --> 00:26:03,185
We have to do
this one last thing for Nueng.

318
00:26:04,305 --> 00:26:05,345
I'll…

319
00:26:07,025 --> 00:26:08,785
handle the temple arrangements.

320
00:26:10,225 --> 00:26:12,545
Fun, you take care
of the hospital paperwork.

321
00:26:13,185 --> 00:26:14,025
Nueng…

322
00:26:15,225 --> 00:26:16,065
Okay.

323
00:26:16,625 --> 00:26:18,625
We'll do this one last thing for Nueng.

324
00:26:41,625 --> 00:26:43,105
How can I help you?

325
00:26:44,785 --> 00:26:46,505
I wanted to ask…

326
00:26:47,065 --> 00:26:51,585
if I'd like the hospital to care for him
during his mother's funeral,

327
00:26:51,665 --> 00:26:53,625
which department should I contact?

328
00:26:53,705 --> 00:26:57,705
You can report the details here first,
then contact Medical Records afterward.

329
00:26:58,345 --> 00:26:59,585
This way, please.

330
00:27:54,185 --> 00:27:56,145
I'm going to rest now.

331
00:27:56,785 --> 00:27:59,265
Tomorrow, we'll go pick up Phupha.

332
00:28:15,305 --> 00:28:16,185
Fun…

333
00:28:19,185 --> 00:28:21,025
There's something
I want to talk to you about.

334
00:28:22,705 --> 00:28:24,105
What is it?

335
00:28:26,225 --> 00:28:28,665
I want the two of us to raise Phupha.

336
00:28:30,625 --> 00:28:33,065
I feel so attached to him.

337
00:28:34,745 --> 00:28:37,425
We've been with him
since he was still in the womb.

338
00:28:37,505 --> 00:28:39,625
I want to take care of him

339
00:28:40,145 --> 00:28:41,985
and watch him grow up.

340
00:28:44,025 --> 00:28:45,945
Can you do this with me?

341
00:28:49,545 --> 00:28:50,985
I feel the same way.

342
00:28:54,865 --> 00:28:58,545
To me, Phupha is a precious thing…

343
00:29:02,185 --> 00:29:03,665
that Nueng left behind for us.

344
00:29:07,465 --> 00:29:08,625
Thank you.

345
00:29:31,225 --> 00:29:32,305
Oh, my goodness.

346
00:29:33,265 --> 00:29:36,145
-Baby Phupha is here.
-Phupha, sweetheart.

347
00:29:43,465 --> 00:29:44,705
Thank you so much.

348
00:29:45,225 --> 00:29:46,185
Thank you.

349
00:29:48,225 --> 00:29:51,145
PHUPHA SRIPITICHOTE
JUNE 5, 2026 - WEIGHT: 2,999 GRAMS

350
00:29:56,505 --> 00:29:57,705
Look at him.

351
00:29:58,825 --> 00:30:00,705
So adorably ugly.

352
00:30:01,505 --> 00:30:02,705
Little Phupha,

353
00:30:03,345 --> 00:30:06,185
come stay with Grandma, okay?

354
00:30:06,265 --> 00:30:07,385
Let's go.

355
00:30:27,505 --> 00:30:30,305
I think I'll stay here
for another couple of days,

356
00:30:30,385 --> 00:30:32,905
then I'll take Phupha back home
with me to Ayutthaya.

357
00:30:35,305 --> 00:30:36,225
Mom.

358
00:30:37,185 --> 00:30:38,025
What?

359
00:30:38,105 --> 00:30:39,265
What are you two doing?

360
00:30:39,865 --> 00:30:41,145
I…

361
00:30:44,185 --> 00:30:46,865
I want to raise Phupha myself.

362
00:30:50,585 --> 00:30:52,265
I want to raise Phupha too.

363
00:30:53,305 --> 00:30:56,105
How are the two of you going to raise him?
This isn't easy, you know.

364
00:30:56,185 --> 00:30:58,545
Raising a newborn is hard.

365
00:30:58,625 --> 00:31:01,945
Both of you work outside the house too.

366
00:31:02,025 --> 00:31:04,265
At night? Forget it.

367
00:31:04,345 --> 00:31:06,185
There's no way you'll get
a full night's sleep,

368
00:31:06,265 --> 00:31:08,825
because babies cry constantly.

369
00:31:09,825 --> 00:31:13,785
And going out together alone?
Going to dinner? Relaxing?

370
00:31:13,865 --> 00:31:15,625
Don't even think about it.

371
00:31:15,705 --> 00:31:16,825
You won't have the chance.

372
00:31:18,185 --> 00:31:21,585
Can you give us a chance
to take care of Phupha?

373
00:31:24,145 --> 00:31:25,345
Please, Mom.

374
00:31:26,065 --> 00:31:28,425
We'll prove to you

375
00:31:28,505 --> 00:31:30,705
that we really can take care of him.

376
00:31:30,785 --> 00:31:32,665
Please, Mom. Please, please.

377
00:31:32,745 --> 00:31:35,105
-Please.
-Can you really do it?

378
00:31:35,945 --> 00:31:37,305
-Please.
-Please, Mom.

379
00:31:37,385 --> 00:31:38,665
I'll think about it first.

380
00:31:51,865 --> 00:31:52,785
That works.

381
00:31:52,865 --> 00:31:55,145
Here you go, sweetheart, your milk.

382
00:32:17,065 --> 00:32:19,305
Hello, yes.

383
00:32:20,065 --> 00:32:24,305
Oh, sure. I'll send the revised draft
via email right away.

384
00:32:32,025 --> 00:32:35,545
There we go. All clean and dry now.
You're comfortable again.

385
00:32:46,465 --> 00:32:48,625
You can sleep, Mom.
I'll take care of Phupha.

386
00:32:49,705 --> 00:32:51,385
-Can you handle it?
-Yes.

387
00:33:06,625 --> 00:33:09,305
That's right. Hold him.

388
00:33:09,385 --> 00:33:12,025
Let's change your diaper.

389
00:33:13,225 --> 00:33:14,465
Fun.

390
00:33:14,545 --> 00:33:16,745
-Yes?
-Did you clean Phupha's belly button yet?

391
00:33:16,825 --> 00:33:18,145
His belly button…

392
00:33:18,225 --> 00:33:20,985
-Oh, right.
-You have to clean it properly.

393
00:33:21,065 --> 00:33:23,105
Otherwise, it could get infected.

394
00:33:23,185 --> 00:33:26,385
You have to be careful,
or Phupha could get a stomachache.

395
00:33:26,945 --> 00:33:30,265
Here, let me explain.

396
00:33:30,345 --> 00:33:33,865
When the umbilical stump is about
to fall off, you have to be extra careful.

397
00:33:34,425 --> 00:33:36,185
Come on.

398
00:33:36,265 --> 00:33:38,505
There, there.

399
00:33:38,585 --> 00:33:39,625
There, there.

400
00:33:39,705 --> 00:33:41,585
Sweetheart.

401
00:33:41,665 --> 00:33:45,505
I'm cleaning your little belly button.

402
00:33:45,585 --> 00:33:48,265
Didn't they teach this
in the class you attended?

403
00:33:49,185 --> 00:33:53,145
They did. I just forgot last night.

404
00:33:53,225 --> 00:33:55,025
You didn't get enough sleep, right?

405
00:33:55,625 --> 00:33:58,825
I told you already,
raising a baby is exhausting.

406
00:33:58,905 --> 00:34:02,145
Go get some rest. I'll handle things here.

407
00:34:20,585 --> 00:34:21,865
Hi, Fun.

408
00:34:23,145 --> 00:34:25,865
-Aunt Wi, hello.
-Hello, dear.

409
00:34:25,945 --> 00:34:27,665
How's the little one doing?

410
00:34:29,105 --> 00:34:31,185
He's doing well.

411
00:34:31,264 --> 00:34:33,705
If everything's fine,

412
00:34:33,784 --> 00:34:35,505
why do you look so down?

413
00:34:36,344 --> 00:34:40,344
Aunt Wi, raising a child
really isn't easy at all.

414
00:34:40,865 --> 00:34:43,585
I guess you need experience
to be able to do it properly.

415
00:34:45,585 --> 00:34:47,505
You don't need experience at all.

416
00:34:47,585 --> 00:34:50,665
Otherwise, how would
first-time parents raise their kids?

417
00:34:50,744 --> 00:34:51,985
Look at me.

418
00:34:52,065 --> 00:34:55,945
I raised Pa since she was tiny, since she
was only two months old. Nobody taught me.

419
00:34:56,025 --> 00:34:59,425
I watched videos and read books,

420
00:34:59,505 --> 00:35:01,785
but in the end, the best thing

421
00:35:01,865 --> 00:35:04,785
is to use your heart to raise them.
Trust me.

422
00:35:05,905 --> 00:35:07,105
Aunt Wi, you're amazing.

423
00:35:08,185 --> 00:35:11,705
Is there some kind of fixed rule
when it comes to raising kids?

424
00:35:11,785 --> 00:35:15,465
Absolutely not.
You just follow the child's lead.

425
00:35:15,545 --> 00:35:17,785
If they're hungry, you feed them milk.

426
00:35:17,865 --> 00:35:20,065
After that, you burp them.

427
00:35:20,145 --> 00:35:24,305
If they fart, poop or pee,
you change their diaper.

428
00:35:24,385 --> 00:35:27,505
And if they seem uncomfortable,
you check if they have a fever

429
00:35:27,585 --> 00:35:29,665
or a stomachache or something.

430
00:35:29,745 --> 00:35:30,985
It's not that hard, dear.

431
00:35:31,065 --> 00:35:35,105
You just get to know them more every day.
You'll start understanding their signals.

432
00:35:35,185 --> 00:35:38,505
It's like a kind of body language
that only the two of you understand.

433
00:35:40,385 --> 00:35:41,945
I want to have that kind of bond too.

434
00:35:43,825 --> 00:35:45,465
It'll happen eventually.

435
00:35:45,545 --> 00:35:47,705
You're the one raising the child,
after all,

436
00:35:47,785 --> 00:35:50,665
so the bond will naturally form
on its own.

437
00:35:51,265 --> 00:35:54,425
Honestly, I don't think
raising a child to adulthood is hard.

438
00:35:54,505 --> 00:35:58,905
What's difficult is raising them
to become a good person. Don't you agree?

439
00:36:00,185 --> 00:36:01,465
That's true.

440
00:36:03,345 --> 00:36:05,065
That's probably much harder.

441
00:36:05,865 --> 00:36:09,825
Oh, Fun, after this,
I won't be home very often anymore.

442
00:36:09,905 --> 00:36:12,505
I'll have to travel back and forth
between Bangkok and Ang Thong

443
00:36:12,585 --> 00:36:14,865
because my sister isn't feeling well.

444
00:36:14,945 --> 00:36:17,025
Make sure you lock your doors
and windows properly.

445
00:36:17,105 --> 00:36:19,945
Thank you so much, Aunt Wi.

446
00:36:20,025 --> 00:36:21,545
You stay strong too, okay?

447
00:36:21,625 --> 00:36:24,945
I hope your sister gets better soon.

448
00:36:25,025 --> 00:36:28,625
I should go check on the baby now.
I'll update you if anything happens.

449
00:36:28,705 --> 00:36:30,945
-See you.
-See you. Take care.

450
00:36:31,025 --> 00:36:32,305
See you.

451
00:37:24,865 --> 00:37:26,785
Please receive this blessing.

452
00:37:27,505 --> 00:37:29,825
For those who always
pay respect to their elders,

453
00:37:29,905 --> 00:37:33,625
four blessings shall grow.

454
00:37:33,705 --> 00:37:36,185
Long life, beauty, happiness

455
00:37:36,265 --> 00:37:39,305
and strength. Blessings upon you.

456
00:37:45,345 --> 00:37:48,625
Nueng, I've made merit for you now.

457
00:37:49,225 --> 00:37:51,265
Don't worry about Phupha.

458
00:37:51,345 --> 00:37:54,345
We'll help raise him well.

459
00:38:10,105 --> 00:38:12,905
It's already been 49 days
since Nueng left us.

460
00:38:17,985 --> 00:38:20,945
I think we should start
packing up Nueng's belongings soon.

461
00:38:41,385 --> 00:38:44,665
AIOON AND PAFUN

462
00:38:50,385 --> 00:38:51,705
-Oon.
-Hmm?

463
00:38:51,785 --> 00:38:53,105
Come look at this.

464
00:39:26,505 --> 00:39:29,105
<i>To Aioon and Pafun,</i>

465
00:39:31,065 --> 00:39:33,905
<i>If you two are reading this letter,</i>

466
00:39:34,705 --> 00:39:37,305
<i>then I'm probably no longer in this world.</i>

467
00:39:38,385 --> 00:39:41,665
<i>Originally,</i>
<i>I planned to come back, find work</i>

468
00:39:42,185 --> 00:39:45,465
<i>and build a small family</i>
<i>with just me and Phupha.</i>

469
00:39:45,545 --> 00:39:48,665
<i>But everything fell apart,</i>

470
00:39:48,745 --> 00:39:49,905
<i>completely.</i>

471
00:39:51,425 --> 00:39:54,105
<i>My panic disorder never seemed to improve.</i>

472
00:39:55,505 --> 00:39:57,905
<i>It felt like</i>
<i>it would stay with me forever.</i>

473
00:39:58,625 --> 00:40:00,465
<i>Every time I had an episode,</i>

474
00:40:01,905 --> 00:40:04,145
<i>it made me feel like</i>

475
00:40:04,225 --> 00:40:06,505
<i>there might not be a tomorrow.</i>

476
00:40:07,745 --> 00:40:10,025
<i>I tried to be strong.</i>

477
00:40:10,585 --> 00:40:13,025
<i>I wanted to become</i>
<i>a good mother for Phupha.</i>

478
00:40:13,745 --> 00:40:15,985
<i>If I don't get the chance to do that,</i>

479
00:40:16,505 --> 00:40:19,105
<i>please take care of Phupha for me.</i>

480
00:40:19,945 --> 00:40:20,945
<i>Please take care of him</i>

481
00:40:22,265 --> 00:40:25,625
<i>and tell him you love him</i>
<i>and hug him on my behalf too.</i>

482
00:40:27,025 --> 00:40:30,385
<i>I know both of you love him</i>
<i>just as much as I do.</i>

483
00:40:31,785 --> 00:40:33,505
<i>Thank you</i>

484
00:40:33,585 --> 00:40:37,425
<i>for staying by my side, taking care of me,</i>

485
00:40:37,505 --> 00:40:41,225
<i>understanding me</i>
<i>and encouraging me all this time.</i>

486
00:40:42,385 --> 00:40:44,065
<i>I love you both so much,</i>

487
00:40:44,145 --> 00:40:46,785
<i>Aioon, Pafun.</i>

488
00:40:53,185 --> 00:40:54,705
NUBNUENG

489
00:41:08,585 --> 00:41:09,945
What are you two doing?

490
00:41:16,705 --> 00:41:17,905
It's a letter from Nueng.

491
00:42:53,425 --> 00:42:54,825
Did the baby fall asleep already?

492
00:42:54,905 --> 00:42:56,065
‎Yeah.

493
00:42:56,145 --> 00:42:57,985
Once he was full,
he fell asleep pretty quickly.

494
00:42:59,185 --> 00:43:03,345
Then eat while you can.
If he cries, I'll go check on him.

495
00:43:05,945 --> 00:43:07,145
Oon.

496
00:43:07,825 --> 00:43:09,505
I'm heading home this afternoon.

497
00:43:10,585 --> 00:43:12,185
I already asked Priaw to call me a car.

498
00:43:12,705 --> 00:43:13,545
‎What?

499
00:43:18,345 --> 00:43:19,225
Mom,

500
00:43:19,305 --> 00:43:22,425
can you not go yet? Please don't take
Phupha away. Stay with us a bit longer.

501
00:43:22,505 --> 00:43:24,225
-Please, Mom.
-Please, Mom.

502
00:43:24,305 --> 00:43:25,745
Please, Mom. Give us another chance.

503
00:43:25,825 --> 00:43:27,625
If I do something wrong,

504
00:43:27,705 --> 00:43:31,145
you can scold me. You can even hit me.
Just please don't take Phupha away.

505
00:43:31,225 --> 00:43:32,825
-Please.
-I'm begging you.

506
00:43:32,905 --> 00:43:33,905
Stop.

507
00:43:34,905 --> 00:43:37,705
Did I ever say
I was taking Phupha with me?

508
00:43:38,825 --> 00:43:41,545
I only said I was going home.

509
00:43:43,425 --> 00:43:45,345
-I love you so much, Mom.
-Thank you.

510
00:43:45,425 --> 00:43:48,385
Thank you so much, Mom.

511
00:43:50,465 --> 00:43:52,105
There, the baby's crying.

512
00:43:52,185 --> 00:43:53,745
-I'll go check on him myself.
-I'll go.

513
00:43:53,825 --> 00:43:56,065
-You barely touched your food.
-It's okay.

514
00:44:00,425 --> 00:44:04,145
See?
Having and raising a child isn't easy.

515
00:44:04,225 --> 00:44:08,505
You can't even enjoy a proper meal
or sit peacefully for a while.

516
00:44:09,385 --> 00:44:11,065
I know, Mom.

517
00:44:13,425 --> 00:44:15,225
This is my family,

518
00:44:17,345 --> 00:44:18,985
the family I've always wanted.

519
00:44:21,025 --> 00:44:23,265
No matter what happens,

520
00:44:24,905 --> 00:44:26,545
I'll get through it.

521
00:44:29,425 --> 00:44:31,105
Good. As long as you understand that.

522
00:44:32,665 --> 00:44:36,145
But if it ever becomes too much, tell me.

523
00:44:44,145 --> 00:44:45,705
Thank you, Mom.

524
00:44:45,785 --> 00:44:48,705
Why are you hugging me now?
I'm not even done eating yet.

525
00:44:48,785 --> 00:44:49,865
Let go.

526
00:44:51,945 --> 00:44:52,825
Look at you.

527
00:44:55,825 --> 00:44:57,585
I love you the most, Mom.

528
00:45:53,545 --> 00:45:54,545
Nueng.

529
00:45:59,265 --> 00:46:00,585
What are you looking at?

530
00:46:16,865 --> 00:46:17,865
Oon…

531
00:46:20,265 --> 00:46:21,705
Thank you so much

532
00:46:22,585 --> 00:46:24,265
for taking such good care of both me

533
00:46:25,185 --> 00:46:27,185
and Phupha.

534
00:46:28,905 --> 00:46:30,305
What are you thanking me for?

535
00:46:31,585 --> 00:46:33,145
I already told you,

536
00:46:33,745 --> 00:46:37,225
if there's ever anything, just tell me.
I'll handle it.

537
00:46:37,985 --> 00:46:38,905
No matter what it is--

538
00:46:38,985 --> 00:46:40,505
I'll do it for you.

539
00:46:57,425 --> 00:46:59,025
Thank you so much.

540
00:47:04,905 --> 00:47:06,425
Please take care of my son for me.

541
00:47:23,785 --> 00:47:25,505
Where are you going?

542
00:47:29,305 --> 00:47:30,265
Nueng.

543
00:47:31,825 --> 00:47:32,985
<i>Thank you.</i>

544
00:47:35,185 --> 00:47:38,105
Nueng, Nueng.

545
00:47:46,305 --> 00:47:47,265
Nueng.

546
00:47:48,305 --> 00:47:49,585
Nueng.

547
00:47:51,065 --> 00:47:52,945
-Nueng.
-Oon.

548
00:48:00,425 --> 00:48:02,505
You were so loud. You woke the baby.

549
00:48:02,585 --> 00:48:04,145
I'll go check on him.

550
00:48:11,065 --> 00:48:15,025
Mommy's here now, sweetheart.

551
00:48:19,465 --> 00:48:22,025
I'm gonna change your diaper, okay?

552
00:48:23,025 --> 00:48:25,545
I'm gonna change your diaper.

553
00:48:26,345 --> 00:48:28,865
You'll feel much more comfortable
after this.

554
00:48:32,825 --> 00:48:34,665
It's okay, sweetheart.

555
00:48:34,745 --> 00:48:37,945
Once we change your diaper,
you'll feel all better.

556
00:48:38,025 --> 00:48:41,225
Let me see.

557
00:48:41,305 --> 00:48:43,745
Let me wipe you clean, okay?
Then you'll be comfy again.

558
00:48:47,385 --> 00:48:49,145
Okay.

559
00:48:49,225 --> 00:48:50,145
-Wait a second.
-Okay.

560
00:48:52,105 --> 00:48:55,185
I'm wiping you,
so you'll feel comfortable.

561
00:49:02,225 --> 00:49:05,145
Oon, don't scream.
He hasn't finished peeing yet.

562
00:49:27,825 --> 00:49:29,345
<i>I can stay home with him.</i>

563
00:49:29,425 --> 00:49:30,505
Don't worry.

564
00:49:30,585 --> 00:49:31,505
Are you sure?

565
00:49:31,585 --> 00:49:33,945
Why is your face all messy like this?
What were you two playing with?

566
00:49:34,025 --> 00:49:35,145
Aioon!

567
00:49:35,865 --> 00:49:37,785
<i>I think some things</i>

568
00:49:38,465 --> 00:49:40,465
are just too intense for a child this age.

569
00:49:40,545 --> 00:49:42,785
It hurts here, here

570
00:49:42,865 --> 00:49:44,745
and here too.

571
00:49:45,385 --> 00:49:46,665
You have a headache, right?

572
00:49:49,785 --> 00:49:52,505
Am I a bad mother, Oon?

573
00:50:22,345 --> 00:50:24,185
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon

